definition.value: A organosulfate oxoanion that is the monoanion obtained by the deprotonation of the sulfate function of callysponginol sulfonic acid A.

A branched amino octasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at positions 3 and 6 by beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man groups and the reducing-end N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue is substituted at position 6 by an alpha-L-fucosyl group.
A carboxyalkyl sulfate that is tetracos-17-en-3-ynoic acid substituted by a sulfooxy group at position 2 (the 2R,17Z stereoisomer).
Any three-ring heterocyclic compound with a skeleton consisting of a pyridine ring ortho-fused to a benzodiazepine.
A geoisomer of dehydrocyclopeptine in which the C=C bond of the benzylidene substituent has Z-configuration.
A geoisomer of dehydrocyclopeptine in which the C=C bond of the benzylidene substituent has E-configuration.
The dianion obtained by deprotonation of the phenol and carboxy functions of  (4-hydroxy-3-nitrophenyl)acetic acid.
An optically active form of cyclopeptine having S-configuration.

An amino nonasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 6 by an alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->6)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group.
A 7,2'-dihydroxy-4'-methoxyisoflavanol that has R configuration at position 3.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate that is ADP substituted at position 3' by an N-methylanthraniloyl group.
An organic anion that is the conjugate base of minocycline, obtained by deprotonation of the two enolic hydroxy groups and protonation of the non-aromatic tertiary amino group.

A signalling molecule produced and used by bacteria participating in quorum sensing, that is, in cell-cell communication to coordinate community-wide regulation of processes such as biofilm formation, virulence, and bioluminescence in populations of bacteria. Such communication can occur both within and between different species of bacteria.
An organic anion that is the conjugate base of novobiocin.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide in which three N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues are linked (1->3), (1->4) and (1->6) to an N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue with unspecified configuration at its anomeric centre.
A branched amino trisaccharide comprising an N -acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residue at the reducing end, to which are (1->3)- and (1->6)-linked  two N -acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine residues.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide comprising a beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine disaccharide, to the galactosyl residue of which are (1->3)- and (1->6)-linked two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues.
A molybdopterin dinucleotide in which the other nucleobase is guanine and the coordinated molybdenum species is MoO2(OH).
An amino disaccharide comprising an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue linked (1->3) to an N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine residue at the reducing end.
An organic anion obtained by selective deprotonation of the 2- and 7-hydroxy groups of norsolorinic acid anthrone.
An organic anion obtained by selective deprotonation of the 2- and 7-hydroxy groups of norsolorinic acid.

A hexacyclic triterpenoid that is an oleanane substituted by an epoxy group between positions 13 and 28 and by hydroxy groups at positions 3, 16, 22 and 28 respectively (the 3beta,16alpha,22alpha stereoisomer). It is isolated from the whole plant of Anagallis arvensis.
An amino disaccharide comprising N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine linked (1->3) to a beta-D-galactose residue.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate, diphosphate and carboxy groups of 2-oxoglutaryl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A linear amino trisaccharide comprised of a (1->3)-linked sequence of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine residues.
Any L-glucoside in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.
Any glucoside with an L-configuration.
A molybdopterin dinucleotide in which the other nucleobase is cytosine and the coordinated molybdenum species is MoO2(OH).
A polyketide that is anthrone bearing four hydroxy substituents at positions 1, 3, 6 and 8 as well as a hexanoyl substituent at position 2.
A linear amino trisaccharide comprising N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3) and (1->4).
A polyketide that is anthraquinone bearing four hydroxy substituents at positions 1, 3, 6 and 8 as well as a hexanoyl substituent at position 2.
A linear amino pentasaccharide comprising three N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues, connected via beta-D-galactose residues in (1->3), (1->4), (1->3) and (1->3) linkages respectively.

A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is the trianion of UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-gamma-D-glutamyl-N(6)-(L-alanyl)-L-lysyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine having anionic diphosphate and carboxy groups and a cationic amino group.
An amino disaccharide comprised of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine linked (1->3) to D-mannose.
A branched amino trisaccharide comprised of two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked (1->4) and (1->6) to N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of 8-oxo-dAMP.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of 8-oxo-dADP.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of 2-oxo-dADP.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the 1-carboxy group of 2-oxoglutaric acid.
A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the 5-hydroxy group to the tertiary amino group of rifampicin; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 16 carbons and 0 double bonds.
An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 17 carbons and 0 double bonds.
An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 16 carbons and 0 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated.
An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 18 carbons and 0 double bonds.
An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 17 carbons and 0 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated.
An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 19 carbons and 0 double bonds.
An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 18 carbons and 0 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated.
An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 20 carbons and 0 double bonds.
An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 19 carbons and 0 double bonds and is 2-hydroxylated.
An N-acyl-15-methylhexadecasphing-4-enine in which the acyl group has 21 carbons and 0 double bonds.
